genresAdvancedInfo.name: muzica bisericeasca
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Muzica bisericeasca, also known as church music, is a religious music genre that is predominantly vocal. It is performed in churches during religious services and ceremonies. The music is characterized by its solemn and peaceful tone, often featuring harmonies and choral arrangements. Muzica bisericeasca is an important part of Romanian Orthodox culture and is used to enhance the spiritual experience of worship.
